EssoraDM integration notes
==========================

EssoraDM is a fork/integration based on Slim Display Manager.

Essora-specific additions:
- binary name: essoradm
- config file: /etc/essoradm.conf
- hooks:
  /etc/essoradm/pre-start
  /etc/essoradm/pre-login
- optional essora-init splash integration:
  assets/splash/essora-boot.png
  assets/essora-init/usr/local/bin/essora-splash
  assets/essora-init/etc/essora-init.d/essora-splash

The Debian postinst configures EssoraDM as the default display manager,
removes Slim from essora-init boot.d, enables the EssoraDM service and
sets default_user in /etc/essoradm.conf to the installed/local user when
that user is not "essora".
